searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib","doc":"Lightweight metrics collection for Elixir applications.","ref":"MetricsLib.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick start - MetricsLib","doc":"# In mix.exs\n    {:metrics_lib, \"~> 0.1\"}\n\n    # In your Application.start/2\n    MetricsLib.Telemetry.attach_defaults()","ref":"MetricsLib.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"Manual instrumentation - MetricsLib","doc":"MetricsLib.increment(\"user.registered\")\n    MetricsLib.gauge(\"queue.depth\", length(queue))\n    MetricsLib.timing(\"payment.latency\", elapsed_ms)","ref":"MetricsLib.html#module-manual-instrumentation"},{"type":"module","title":"Dashboard - MetricsLib","doc":"Mount `MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live` in your Phoenix router:\n\n    live \"/metrics\", MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live\n\nThe dashboard auto-updates every 5 seconds via Phoenix PubSub.","ref":"MetricsLib.html#module-dashboard"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.gauge/3","doc":"Set a gauge to an absolute value.\n\nGauges represent a current state (queue depth, active connections, etc.).\nOnly the last written value per key is kept.","ref":"MetricsLib.html#gauge/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - MetricsLib.gauge/3","doc":"MetricsLib.gauge(\"vm.memory_mb\", :erlang.memory(:total) / 1_048_576)\n    MetricsLib.gauge(\"queue.depth\", 42, %{queue: \"email\"})","ref":"MetricsLib.html#gauge/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.increment/3","doc":"Increment a counter by `value` (default 1).\n\nCounters accumulate within each aggregation window and are reset after\neach snapshot is broadcast.","ref":"MetricsLib.html#increment/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - MetricsLib.increment/3","doc":"MetricsLib.increment(\"http.requests\")\n    MetricsLib.increment(\"http.requests\", 1, %{method: \"GET\", status: 200})","ref":"MetricsLib.html#increment/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.measure/3","doc":"Measure the execution time of `fun` and record it as a timing.\n\nReturns the function's return value.","ref":"MetricsLib.html#measure/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - MetricsLib.measure/3","doc":"result = MetricsLib.measure(\"render.template\", fn -> render_page() end)","ref":"MetricsLib.html#measure/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.timing/3","doc":"Record a timing sample in milliseconds.\n\nAll samples within a window are aggregated into avg/p50/p95/p99/max.","ref":"MetricsLib.html#timing/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - MetricsLib.timing/3","doc":"start = System.monotonic_time(:millisecond)\n    do_work()\n    MetricsLib.timing(\"job.duration\", System.monotonic_time(:millisecond) - start)\n\n    # With tags\n    MetricsLib.timing(\"db.query\", 12.5, %{table: \"users\", op: \"select\"})","ref":"MetricsLib.html#timing/3-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib.Aggregator","doc":"Periodically reads raw samples from `MetricsLib.Storage`, computes\naggregates (avg, p95, p99, rate/s), broadcasts results via PubSub, and\nkeeps the last 60 snapshots in state for the dashboard history.","ref":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.html"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.history/0","doc":"Return up to the last 60 snapshots (newest first).","ref":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.html#history/0"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.latest/0","doc":"Return the most recent snapshot, or nil if none computed yet.","ref":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.html#latest/0"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"MetricsLib.Aggregator.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live","doc":"Real-time LiveView dashboard for MetricsLib.\n\nMount this view in your router with:\n\n    live \"/metrics\", MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live.html"},{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router","doc":"Plug router that serves the LiveView dashboard at `/metrics`.","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Embedding in an existing Phoenix app - MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router","doc":"In your `router.ex`:\n\n    scope \"/admin\" do\n      pipe_through [:browser]\n      forward \"/metrics\", MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router\n    end\n\nOr mount the LiveView directly for full control:\n\n    live \"/metrics\", MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.html#module-embedding-in-an-existing-phoenix-app"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.browser/2","doc":"","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.html#browser/2"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.call/2","doc":"Callback invoked by Plug on every request.","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.init/1","doc":"Callback required by Plug that initializes the router\nfor serving web requests.","ref":"MetricsLib.Dashboard.Router.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib.Storage","doc":"ETS-backed storage for raw metric samples.\n\nTwo tables are used internally:\n\n- `:metrics_kv`      — `:set`, holds counters (atomically incremented) and gauge values.\n- `:metrics_samples` — `:bag`, holds timing samples (many rows per key).\n\nBoth tables are `:public` so any process writes directly without going\nthrough a GenServer bottleneck. `read_concurrency: true` optimises reads.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.all_kv/0","doc":"Return all counter and gauge rows.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#all_kv/0"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.all_samples/0","doc":"Return all timing sample rows.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#all_samples/0"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.clear/0","doc":"Delete all rows from both tables.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#clear/0"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.gauge/3","doc":"Insert (overwrite) a gauge value.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#gauge/3"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.increment/3","doc":"Atomically increment a counter.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#increment/3"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Storage.timing/3","doc":"Append a timing sample.","ref":"MetricsLib.Storage.html#timing/3"},{"type":"module","title":"MetricsLib.Telemetry","doc":"Attaches handlers to `:telemetry` events emitted by Phoenix and Ecto.\n\nCall `attach_defaults/1` once in your application's `start/2`, or pass an\nexplicit list of event specs to `attach/1` for fine-grained control.","ref":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - MetricsLib.Telemetry","doc":"# application.ex\n    def start(_type, _args) do\n      MetricsLib.Telemetry.attach_defaults(repo: MyApp.Repo)\n      # ...\n    end","ref":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.attach_defaults/1","doc":"Attach handlers for the most common Phoenix + Ecto events.\n\nOptions:\n- `:repo` – your Ecto repo module (used to build the telemetry prefix).\n  Defaults to guessing from the OTP app name.","ref":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.html#attach_defaults/1"},{"type":"function","title":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.detach/0","doc":"Detach the default handler (useful in tests).","ref":"MetricsLib.Telemetry.html#detach/0"},{"type":"extras","title":"MetricsLib","doc":"# MetricsLib\n\nLightweight metrics collection for Elixir applications — counters, gauges, timings — with a real-time LiveView dashboard powered by Phoenix PubSub and ETS.\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/metrics_lib.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/metrics_lib)","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Features - MetricsLib","doc":"- **Three metric types** — counters, gauges, timings (with auto-computed avg/p50/p95/p99)\n- **Zero-bottleneck writes** — ETS public table; any process writes directly, no GenServer round-trip\n- **Telemetry integration** — one call to capture Phoenix request times, Ecto query times, and any custom `:telemetry` events\n- **Real-time dashboard** — Phoenix LiveView page that auto-updates every 5 s without a page reload\n- **Hex-friendly** — documented with ExDoc, typed with `@spec`, easy to embed in any Phoenix app","ref":"readme.html#features"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - MetricsLib","doc":"```elixir\n# mix.exs\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:metrics_lib, \"~> 0.1\"}\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quick start - MetricsLib","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#quick-start"},{"type":"extras","title":"1. Attach Telemetry handlers (optional but recommended) - MetricsLib","doc":"```elixir\n# lib/my_app/application.ex\ndef start(_type, _args) do\n  MetricsLib.Telemetry.attach_defaults(repo: MyApp.Repo)\n  # ...\nend\n```\n\nThis captures `phoenix.router_dispatch` and `ecto.query` timings automatically.","ref":"readme.html#1-attach-telemetry-handlers-optional-but-recommended"},{"type":"extras","title":"2. Manual instrumentation - MetricsLib","doc":"```elixir\n# Counter — increments an integer\nMetricsLib.increment(\"user.registered\")\nMetricsLib.increment(\"http.errors\", 1, %{status: 500})\n\n# Gauge — set a current value\nMetricsLib.gauge(\"queue.depth\", Enum.count(pending_jobs))\n\n# Timing — record elapsed milliseconds\nMetricsLib.timing(\"payment.charge\", elapsed_ms, %{provider: \"stripe\"})\n\n# Measure — wraps a function, records its wall time\nresult = MetricsLib.measure(\"heavy_computation\", fn -> compute() end)\n```","ref":"readme.html#2-manual-instrumentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"3. Mount the dashboard - MetricsLib","doc":"```elixir\n# lib/my_app_web/router.ex\nscope \"/\" do\n  pipe_through :browser\n  live \"/metrics\", MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live\nend\n```\n\nNavigate to `/metrics` — you'll see live-updating tables of all your metrics, refreshed every 5 seconds.","ref":"readme.html#3-mount-the-dashboard"},{"type":"extras","title":"How it works - MetricsLib","doc":"```\nYour code / Phoenix / Ecto\n        │\n        ▼  :telemetry events + direct calls\n  MetricsLib.Storage  ◄── ETS :bag table (public, fast writes)\n        │\n        ▼  every 5 s\n  MetricsLib.Aggregator  ──► computes avg/p50/p95/p99\n        │\n        ▼  Phoenix.PubSub broadcast\n  MetricsLib.Dashboard.Live  ──► pushes diff to browser via WebSocket\n```","ref":"readme.html#how-it-works"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuration - MetricsLib","doc":"The aggregation interval can be changed at startup via application config:\n\n```elixir\n# config/config.exs  (not yet wired — pass as child spec option)\n{MetricsLib.Aggregator, interval_ms: 10_000}\n```","ref":"readme.html#configuration"},{"type":"extras","title":"Documentation - MetricsLib","doc":"Generate locally:\n\n```bash\nmix docs\nopen doc/index.html\n```","ref":"readme.html#documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - MetricsLib","doc":"MIT","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}